==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chlorophane
<hw>Chlo"ro*phane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chlwro`s</grk> light green + <?/ to show: cf. F.
<ets>chlorophane</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
variety of fluor spar, which, when heated, gives a beautiful emerald
green light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The yellowish green pigment in
the inner segment of the cones of the retina. See
<er>Chromophane</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chlorophyll</ent>⟦br⟧
